name: No 1
description:
A Gladstone Montrose bone china tea trio, dates from the 1950's.

Carefully wrapped in tissue paper, nestled in a recycled gift box with its very own polaroid style photograph and letter; all tied up with a bow.  

A perfect gift for that tea drinking, china loving connoisseur. A pre-loved heirloom in the making.

The box dimensions are approximately 20 cm x 20 cm x 10 cm.

name: Postcards No 1, 2 & 3
description:
The twirly stand is all neatly packed with Postcards of Pretty.

Each parcel contains 6 postcards, two of each image, one to keep and one to share, all wrapped in their own simple bag.

The uses are endless, to say thank you, I love you, to decorate a pretty corner of a shelf or wall.
